    "They stated that a recurrent network is a viable approach for dealing with observations from multiple states.",
    "However, it presents no systematic benefits compared to stacking these observations in the input layer of a plain CNN.",
    "Moreno-Vera (2019) proposed a similar approach using DDQN instead of DQN.",
    "Wang et al. (2016) proposed using a new deep neural network architecture called Dueling Networks instead of classical (well-known) architectures such as CNNs, LSTMs, or MLPs to improve model-free reinforcement learning methods.",
